        "name": "Marwari",
        "type": "language_region",
        "category": "custom",
        "district": "Jodhpur, Pali, Nagaur, Barmer, Jalore",
        "speakers": "~14 million (Rajasthan share)",
        "state": "Rajasthan",
        "source": "Sikhwal Manchitrawali (16th ed.) + Census 2011 (mother tongue)",
        "lastUpdated": "2026-07-12",
        "icon": "🗣",
        "notes": {
          "facts": [
            "Rajasthan's most-spoken dialect — Marwar region's language, closely related to Gujarati.",
            "Rich literary tradition: 'Dhola-Maru', 'Padmavat' (Malik Muhammad Jayasi's Hindi is stylistically Marwari-influenced), 'Vachanika Rathore'.",
            "Written in the Mahajani (Marwari merchant) script; modern usage has shifted to Devanagari."
          ]
        },
        "districts_included": [
          "Barmer",
          "Jalore",
          "Jodhpur",
          "Nagaur",
          "Pali"
