        "name": "Mewari",
        "type": "language_region",
        "category": "custom",
        "district": "Udaipur, Chittor, Rajsamand, Bhilwara, Pratapgarh",
        "speakers": "~5 million",
        "state": "Rajasthan",
        "source": "Sikhwal Manchitrawali (16th ed.) + Census 2011 (mother tongue)",
        "lastUpdated": "2026-07-12",
        "icon": "🗣",
        "notes": {
          "facts": [
            "Language of the Mewar region — softer, more Sanskritised than Marwari to the west.",
            "Preserved in Sisodia court chronicles: 'Ekling Mahatmya', 'Vir Vinod', 'Amar Kavya Vamshavali'.",
            "Meera Bai's bhajans are in a Braj-Mewari mixed dialect that shaped North Indian bhakti poetry."
          ]
        },
        "districts_included": [
          "Bhilwara",
          "Chittorgarh",
          "Pratapgarh",
          "Rajsamand",
          "Udaipur"
        ]
