        "category": "custom",
        "district": "Sikar, Jhunjhunu, Churu",
        "speakers": "~3 million",
        "state": "Rajasthan",
        "source": "Sikhwal Manchitrawali (16th ed.) + Census 2011 (mother tongue)",
        "lastUpdated": "2026-07-12",
        "icon": "🗣",
        "notes": {
          "facts": [
            "Language of the Shekhawati region (Sikar-Jhunjhunu-Churu) — a Marwari-Dhundhari transitional dialect.",
            "The Marwari merchant diaspora (Birlas, Bajajs, Poddars, Goenkas) originated here — spread Shekhawati vocabulary into Kolkata and Bombay commerce.",
            "Preserved through Shekhawati folk songs and the Kayasth poet Gopinath's 19th c. compositions."
          ]
        },
        "districts_included": [
          "Churu",
          "Jhunjhunu",
          "Sikar"
        ]
      }
